To prevent Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attacks, you should properly encode any user input before including it in the HTML response. One common method to achieve this is by using OWASP's ESAPI library or similar encoding functions. Here is an updated version of your servlet code that addresses the XSS vulnerability:

